.TH "tipc_send_group_mcast" 9 "tipc_send_group_mcast" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tipc_send_group_mcast \- send message to all members with given identity
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" tipc_send_group_mcast
.BI "(struct socket *sock "  ","
.BI "struct msghdr *m "  ","
.BI "int dlen "  ","
.BI "long timeout "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sock" 12
socket structure
.IP "m" 12
message to send
.IP "dlen" 12
total length of message data
.IP "timeout" 12
timeout to wait for wakeup
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Called from function \fBtipc_sendmsg\fP, which has done all sanity checks
.SH "RETURN"
the number of bytes sent on success, or errno
